VE has problems processing the following statement in the getTabResults method:
  tabResults.getSelectionModel().addListSelectionListener

Francesc Ros?s,
As a workaround until we resolve the bug, you can change the code to set the selectionModel as a seperate object and add the listener. Here's the code in getTabResults():
if (tabResults == null) {
	tabResults = new JTable();
	ListSelectionModel sm = tabResults.getSelectionModel();
	sm.addListSelectionListener(new ListSelectionListener() {
		public void valueChanged(ListSelectionEvent e) {
			if (e.getValueIsAdjusting()) {
				return;
			}
			int selRow = getTabResults().getSelectedRow();
			if (selRow == -1) {
				getTaEnglish().setText("");
				getTaCatalan().setText("");
				return;
			}
			rowToFields();
		} // valueChanged()
	} // ListSelectionListener
	);
	}
return tabResults;
